3 Quick start
*************

The simplest path is the positional API: mark a region or point as
pending, then atomically replace it when the answer arrives.

3.1 Mark a region for rewrite
=============================

     (let ((tok (pending-region (line-beginning-position)
                                (line-end-position)
                                "rewriting")))
       ;; ... kick off async work ...
       (pending-finish tok "the new text"))

3.2 Mark a single point for insertion
=====================================

     (let ((tok (pending-insert (point) "Calling Claude")))
       (run-at-time 2 nil (lambda () (pending-finish tok "Hello!"))))

3.3 Cancel from point
=====================

Place the cursor on a placeholder and run ‘M-x pending-cancel-at-point’.
The placeholder's overlay also binds ‘RET’ and ‘mouse-1’ to the same
command via ‘pending-region-map’, so a single ‘RET’ on the highlighted
region cancels the in-flight work.

3.4 Show the lighter mode
=========================

     M-x global-pending-lighter-mode

   The mode-line gains a small ‘[N⏳~Ks]’ summary while any placeholders
are active.  Clicking the lighter opens ‘pending-list’.


