7 Indicator modes
*****************

Choose a visual via the ‘:indicator’ keyword to ‘pending-make’.  The
simple positional API always uses ‘:lighter’; the rich API defaults to
‘:spinner’.

Indicator   Visual                    Use when
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
‘:spinner’  Animated glyph + label    Duration unknown but the library
            (default).                should look alive.
                                      
‘:percent’  Spinner glyph + bar +     Caller can supply a fraction in
            percent.                  ‘[0.0, 1.0]’.
                                      
‘:eta’      Spinner glyph + bar +     Caller has a rough guess at total
            remaining-seconds         wall-clock seconds.
            estimate.                 
‘:lighter’  Static badge.  No         Visual marker only; no progress to
            animation.                convey.

   The ‘:eta’ indicator uses a piecewise-asymptotic formula:

   • 0 \le ratio \le 0.8 -- linear: fraction = ratio.
   • 0.8 < ratio \le 1.0 -- linear, slope 0.75: hits 0.95 at ratio = 1.
   • ratio > 1.0 -- asymptote: 1 - 0.05 e^{-(ratio-1)}.

   This avoids the "100% but still working" effect that bothers users.
The bar saturates toward (but never reaches) 100% past the deadline, so
callers can rely on "not done until I say so."

   Spinner styles ship with: ‘dots-1’, ‘dots-2’, ‘line’, ‘arc’, ‘clock’.
Add your own:

     (add-to-list 'pending-spinner-styles
                  '(my-style . ["a" "b" "c"]))


