16 Development
**************

16.1 Building
=============

This package uses Eask (https://github.com/emacs-eask/cli) for build
automation, with a Makefile wrapper.

     # Install dependencies
     eask install-deps

     # Compile (warning-free)
     eask compile

     # Run tests (72 ERT tests as of v0.1.0)
     eask test ert pending-test.el

     # All-in-one via Make
     make compile
     make test
     make docs       # build doc/pending.info
     make clean

16.2 Generating the manual
==========================

The Texinfo source lives at ‘doc/pending.texi’; the built ‘pending.info’
ships in the package.

     make info       # build doc/pending.info
     make html       # build doc/pending.html (preview)
     make clean-docs

16.3 Interactive development
============================

     ;; Reload the library after editing
     (unload-feature 'pending t)
     (load-file "pending.el")

     ;; Run a single test
     M-x ert RET pending-test/scheduled-to-resolved RET

     ;; Open the demo
     M-x pending-demo

16.4 Contributing
=================

Bug reports and pull requests are welcome via GitHub.  When filing an
issue, please include the Emacs version, whether you are running
graphical or terminal Emacs, steps to reproduce, and a backtrace if
applicable.

   When sending a PR, please match the existing code style (lexical
binding, double-dash for internal symbols, comprehensive docstrings),
add ERT tests for new behaviour, ensure ‘eask compile’ is warning-free
and ‘eask test’ is green, and run ‘M-x checkdoc’ on touched files.


